<p><b>What is the difference between ISO 9001 and ISO 22000?</b> ISO 9001 and ISO 22000 are two different standards. ISO 9001 is a quality management system standard that can be used by any organization, regardless of size or industry. ISO 22000 is a food safety management system standard that can be used by organizations in the food and beverage industry.</p>
<p><b>Does ISO 22000 include HACCP?</b> ISO 22000 integrates the principles of the Hazard Analysis and Critical Control Point (HACCP) system and application steps developed by the Codex Alimentarius Commission. By means of auditable requirements, it combines the HACCP plan with prerequisite programmes.</p>
